==Japanese==

===Etymology 1===
Originally a compound of {{etyl|ojp|ja}} elements {{compound|ja|こ|tr1=ko|t1=(''pronoun'') this|の|tr2=no|t2=possessive, modifies following noun}}. {{l|ja|こ}} as a pronoun is no longer used individually in modern Japanese.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|acc=h|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|ja|此の}}, {{l|ja|斯の}}

====Adnominal====
{{ja-pos|adnominal}}

# ''([[deictically]])'' [[this]] ... (near the speaker)
#: {{ja-usex|'''この'''車は緑です。|'''この''' くるま は みどり です。|'''This''' car is green.}}
# ''([[anaphorically]])'' [[this]] ... I am talking about (only the speaker knows)

=====Usage notes=====
* This term can only be used when followed by a noun or noun phrase. It cannot be used as a standalone pronoun. Examples:
** '''Correct''':
**: {{ja-usex-inline|'''この'''[[色]]が好きです。|'''^この''' いろ が すき です。|I like '''this''' color.}}
*** A noun follows ''kono''.
** '''Incorrect''':
**: {{ja-usex-inline|'''この'''が好きです。|'''^この''' が すき です。|I like '''this''' ...}}
*** There must be a noun in place of the "...".
*** Using ''kono'' in this way is comparable to using English {{m|en|the}} without a noun after it (*''I like the.'').
* Almost always spelled in hiragana as {{lang|ja|この}}.

